  "body": "### Component\r\n\r\nForge\r\n\r\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\r\n\r\n- [X] Foundry\r\n- [X] Foundryup\r\n\r\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\r\n\r\nforge create\r\n\r\n### Operating System\r\n\r\n_No response_\r\n\r\n### Describe the bug\r\n\r\nThe issue was discovered and detailed in this comment for a separate pull request of mine, related to forge run . Project member onbjerg requested a separate issue for this, as it also affects the existing forge create behaviour:\r\nhttps://github.com/foundry-rs/foundry/pull/1258#issuecomment-1104338256\r\n\r\nA fix for this (ignore the run.rs changes) is on one of my branches:\r\nhttps://github.com/december1981/foundry/commit/b623120df99f6a074ab94523d00e3972189a4bf2\r\n\r\nA  further suggested improvement for using json encoded argument files:\r\nhttps://github.com/december1981/foundry/commit/e9e369a4fbde4e49f9ee096b6607acf3182911d0\r\n",
